arStrings.szText: What a curious question. Birdsong on the air, the rustling of leaves, the humming of little insects. All these things deserve life.
The Dregs would’ve stomped that out. They twisted the plants for their poison-making, they choked the soil.
It wasn’t the first time this place died. Once, it was called Toraja, we think. Piles and piles of bones litter the earth. Who knows what happened? It is a mass grave now... one that needs tending.
